parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause loud noise, startling the driver and occupants, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from flying glass.
The failure of the child safety lock system can lead to unlocked doors while driving, posing a risk to the safety of children and occupants.
The windshield cracking or breaking easily can obstruct the driver's view, causing accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.

delayed or sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the lane assist system can cause the vehicle to deviate from its intended path, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Vehicle deviating from its intended path

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Various other issues, such as oxygen-depleting gases, wind noise, and Apple Play connectivity problems, can cause discomfort, distraction, or safety risks.
The inadvertent unlatching of seatbelts can lead to a significant safety risk, particularly in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: seatbelts require multiple attempts to latch
seatbelts unlatch without any external force or impact
and alarm lights and warning messages may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty with seatbelt latching can lead to frustration and distraction while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Seatbelts are hard to click together
the receiving end of the seatbelt is recessed too far into the chair
the male part of the seatbelt has a bend/angle that requires pushing the receiver end to the side to get the right angle to buckle
and booster seats may not fit properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the child safety lock system can lead to the doors unlocking while the vehicle is in motion, putting children at risk of opening the doors and potentially falling out or getting injured.
symptoms: The child safety lock button causes an audible cycling of the door locks
followed by an error message on the dash stating "Child Safety Lock Failure". The issue can occur intermittently or regularly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, such as the lane departure system, forward collision system, and check engine light, leading to an unsafe driving experience.
symptoms: The lane departure system and forward collision system go offline
the check engine light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the door lock and alarm system can cause unnecessary distractions and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The alarm starts going off when locking the doors
and two alerts are sent to the phone through Bluelink
showing a Rear Occupancy Alert and a Panic Alert.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The infotainment system constantly disconnects from the cell phone
requiring the driver to reconnect and adjust settings while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall of the tow hitch wiring can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents or property damage.
